Yiyun Zhang(Benny)
yz523
CS380
HW5
==========================================
This homework is a programming assignment.
The first part is the improvement of the evaluation function for Minimax player.
After playing several times of Othello game, I found the pieces in the edges have extremely high value.
It is because it can lead to huge amout of vertical and diagonal changes.
Therefore I make these poisitons hava extra value in the evaluation function.
The new evaluation function is in the OthelloMinimax.java class file,
and the original minimax player has been changed to use this new evaluation function.

The second part is the Othello player that extend the original Ohtello player class,
using MonteCarlo Tree search algorithm. The class is created following the assignment instructions.
For each function, the comments explains how it follow the requirements and the behavior.

To run this program, first enter make, which will produce the class files.
After that, enter java HW5 [depth], and the program will automatically run two tournaments.
(The depth should be a number(integer)).
The first tournament is a OthelloRandomPlayer vs a Minimax player with a chosen depth.
The second tournament is a OthelloRandomPlayer vs MonteCarlo player.
==========================================
Sample output:
yz523@tux3:~/cs380/hw5$ make
javac -g HW5.java
javac -g Test.java
yz523@tux3:~/cs380/hw5$ java HW5 3
